@startuml CreateReaction

actor User as "Users"
boundary "BlogDetailPage" as View 
participant ":reactionRoute" as Route 
control "authMiddleware" as Auth 
control "reactionController" as Controller 
participant ":reactionService" as Service 
entity "reactionCommentModel" as Model
database "MongoDB" as MongoDB 
hide footbox

    User -> View: 1. Hover/Click "Like" button
    activate User
    activate View

    View -> View: 2. Show icon list
    activate View
    deactivate View

    opt Cancel Reaction
        View --> User: 2.1. Move cursor away / Click "Delete" icon
    end

    User -> View: 3. Click specific reaction icon

    View -> Route: 4. POST /api/v1/reaction { commentId, reactionType }
    activate Route
    Route -> Auth: 5. authenticateUser(req, res, next)
    activate Auth
    ref over User, MongoDB : Verifies token


    Auth -> Controller: 6. next(req)
    deactivate Auth
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Service: 7. addReaction(reactionData, userId)
    activate Service

    Service -> Model: 8. insertOne(reactionData, userId)
    activate Model

    Model -> MongoDB: 9. Insert new reaction
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB --> Model: 10. Return created reaction
    deactivate MongoDB

    Model --> Service: 11. Return result
    deactivate Model

    Service --> Controller: 12. Return created reaction
    deactivate Service

    Controller --> Route: 13. 201 Created + reaction
    deactivate Controller

    Route --> View: 14. Render created reaction
    deactivate Route

    View --> User: 15. Display created reaction by the comment
    deactivate View
    deactivate User

@enduml